column2: Overcast and southeast wind at 5 mph.  18 feet to bottom.
Southwest wind at 10 mph.  18 feet to bottom.  Gold-tan sun at shoreline.
Southwest wind 15 mph and sunny.  17 feet to bottom.
Southeast wind at 5 mph and sunny.  Rained on 9/14 and 9/15.  19 feet to bottom.
West wind at 10 mph and sunny.  19 feet to bottom.
West wind at 15 mph and overcast.  18 feet to bottom.
Southwest wind at 8 mph and sunny.  18 feet to bottom.
Southeast wind at 10 mph and overcast.  17 feet to bottom.
Southwest wind at 10 mph and sunny.  17.5 feet to bottom.
West wind at 5 mph and overcast.  18 feet to bottom.
Overcast- southwest wind at 5 mph- 18' depth- and chilly.
Ice out on 4/9/99.  First loon on 4/10- pair of mallards and three geese on 4/5.
17.5 depth- windy- and the temperature of the water is 52 degrees.
Overcast- sprinkling- and yellow pollen around lake shore.
Sunny. Wind at 7 mph. Heavy rains during the last week.
Lots of rain prior and there is a light wind.
Over 2" rain yesterday- sunny- and light southeast wind- a quiet Saturday on the lake.
Sunny- north wind at 7 mph- and 2 loons observing.
Ice out on April 21- 2001.  Panfish in - very tasty!  Overcast and a 5 mph wind.
Wind at 5 mph and it is a nice- bright day at times.
Bright day- wind at 5-15 mph- a lot of green pollen on top and in the lake along the shore.
Lake seems to be clearing from the pollen blast- wind about 5 mph- and is a nice day.
End of heat wave!  Beautiful day.
Overcast- the temperature is 76 degrees- wind about 5 mph- and it is a nice day.
Finding dead suckers on lake's shore- two gulls on the lake and there are lots of eagles.
Overcast dark day and it is very hard to see in the water.  North wind at about 5 mph.
Ice out 4-16. Odd spring- trouble getting on water.

column1: Wind about 10mph. Fish starting to come in.

column2: Beautiful sunny day.  Loon closely watching us.
mama duck + 3 "babies" swimming around. (3 babies out of 7 survived.)
Otter seen in lake for the first time in many years and the amount of fish seems to be very low because of the otter.
Sunny skies- no clouds. 81?F 81?F sunny without a cloud in sight.
